<username>DAZZ__</username><Time>1595381924209< /Time><Rating>1</Rating>< text>
I have been with Personal Express Insurance for 3 years for my auto insurance, I even added my partner for his auto insurance. They go through National General Insurance. Throughout the years, I realize their system is a bit old. The website seems not friendly to use. Now a days accessibility to your information is a must. They randomly would raise the prices, we did not mind at first. Now with our home being insurance with them it we got a little disgruntled. Our house recently had major damages which required home insurance. The claims representative we had the worst customer service. It seemed like contacting them was a hassle. We would email them, call them. NO RESPONSE.

My partner and I were really frustrated at this point. We did not have a home and were staying in a hotel for months. We would got for weeks not getting an update from this claims rep. We finally decided to reach out to their manager, which helped us.

We pay all this money for insurance on our vehicles and our home. We decided to move elsewhere. It was not about the money but about the customer service for us. I would honestly recommend another company. The prices are great, but the quality/service is not great. At this point when we finally decided to move home. We switch to another insurance company.</text>

Personal Express is amazing...until you actually need them.  Setting up, the occasional review of coverage, any changes the staff was kind and professional.  But if you need them they will find a way out of covering you through tricky wording.  I was hit by a car and they opened a claim, paid me very quickly for the receipts I sent in and after about a month they came back and said just kidding, you're not covered because of this and this, even though every person I talked to in their company and other insurance companies said I'd be covered.  It all boiled down to the wording that just seems like they could get out of covering you in one way or another no matter what happened.  Watch out!  You'll think you're covered when you really aren't.</Text>

<user>112888872685294275825< /user>< user_name>
Josh J</user_name>
< Date>
1612204522540<//Date>
< Rating>
1</Rating>
< text>
Diabetics, avoid this location!

I've been coming to Riverside Medical for my medical care ever since I was a child, many of their doctors have been excellent to have over the years, however I couldn't recommend against their urgent care center any more.

Over the phone, their receptionist is disrespectful, sighing upon answering the phone and responding to questions with a poor, dismissive attitude.

When I came in for assistance with a medical issue, the DO had no idea how to assist me with my juvenile diabetes or how to help a diabetic patient with a pump. (It's no different than injections in many ways.) Despite this fact, he had no problem prescribing a dose of 20 units of insulin - five times the amount necessary to treat my blood sugar at the time. He changed my insulin prescription in such a way that I now need to go and change it again through my endocrinologist despite the fact that an urgent care doctor shouldn't be able to do so or have any need to. Another thing, this DO seems to believe that a type 1 diabetic should be injecting 100 units per day of insulin! Thats twice as much as I take daily, bolus and basal rates included! Finally, when my blood sugar was within a reasonable range, they insisted we continue waiting until my sugars would have come down to a range which is considered low for type 1s. When I arrived home, after receiving far more insulin than required, my blood sugar was dangerously low to the point of nearly passing out.

Simply put, this place prefers fast, hands off treatment that will get you out of the door as soon as possible, damn the consequences.

All in all, I am absolutely appalled at the lack of professionalism and care at this incredibly dangerous practice.</text>

I went to Urgent Care for a work related injury. The staff were very helpful and explained to me the process of WC as I had never been hurt on the job before and knew absolutely nothing about what to do. She got the paperwork rolling and had me in to see the Doctor within 15 - 20 minutes.
Dr. Tenenbaum was AMAZING. He asked specific and thorough questions and made eye contact the whole time! If I had a question, he took the time to explain the answer to me in layman's terms. He was very gentle and conscious that I was in a lot of pain and seemed sympathetic about it.
I have been to this Urgent Care several times in the past for more common ailments like the flu and have always been treated with courtesy and respect. The wait times do vary depending on how many people are there, but I've always been happy with my experiences.</text>

<time>1353283203799< /time><rate>5</rate><text>Ever since my little girl took her first steps she has wanted to perform.  ‚ÄúPut on a show!"
She would convince all of her friends to participate, and direct them in dancing, singing, or any other performance she could think up.

She made me promise I would help her become an actor.  So one day she came to me with a ‚Äúprivate invitation‚Äù from someone we had never had contact with before.  They told her how special she was, and how they were inviting a small, exclusive group of talented actors to audition.  So I took her to this small, exclusive group of hundreds of children, to audition for some folks claiming connections with the Disney Company.

What I discovered was my beautiful daughter was painfully shy, unable to look another person in the eye while talking, actually incapable of answering questions asked of her.  She looked good on camera, but even with 45 minutes prep time she was unable to perform a 30 second spot with a teleprompter.

Despite what I saw as an obvious rejection, within an hour a representative called and told me that from the hundreds of talented actors, my girl was one of a handful whom they wished to be associated with.  For a mere fifteen thousand dollars, round trip airfare to Orlando FL, and two weeks hotel stay she could participate in the largest cattle call audition on the planet.  We graciously declined their offer of instantaneous fame.

Now I've learned, and accepted a long time ago, that in certain instances children exhibit more respect, listen, and learn quicker from a stranger than from their parents.  That‚Äôs why we seek out the finest teachers available.  I began looking for a reputable acting coach with contacts, and who understood how the entertainment business worked.  My search led me to Ms. Mae of 3-2-1 Acting Studios.

When they called me in and described what they liked, and why they wanted to represent her, it seemed as if they were talking about an entirely different person.

They loved her performance, (I‚Äôve always loved her acting), but what surprised me was when they said how impressed at how poised she was, looking them in the eyes when she spoke, her open friendly personality, the ease at which she was able to talk with them, the intelligent questions she asked‚Ä¶  In essence Mae and John had transformed a shy, aloof little girl into a professional actor.

3-2-1- has a wide variety of classes all designed to help your actor achieve their goal in the highly competitive entertainment industry.  What I particularly loved was how dedicated they are in teaching you how the business works.  Weather you're in front of the camera, or at an audition they teach you what you need, enabling you to act like a seasoned professional. <rate>5<//rate><Date>1387396642465<//Date><userid>104591465142583795386<//userid>< Text>
We absolutely love Ms. Mae and her amazing acting studios, but first, the reasons we feel that way about 3-2-1 so much:
My daughter, who is now 9, has exhibited the desire to act for most of her life -- in fact ever since she wanted to run up on stage during a community theatre performance when she was 2 years-old!  When she turned 4, I realized I had to do something with her urge to perform/ham it up/what-have-you.  My wife and I decided it wouldn't be a bad idea to have her take acting lessons, if indeed any classes existed for a child that young.
We were living in La Crescenta at the time, and thus 'discovered' 3-2-1 accidentally because it wasn't far from where we lived -- and they taught kids as young as my daughter was!  As a matter of fact, I believe our girl was one of the first 4 year-olds that Ms. Mae's studio taught, and now it seems like there are quite a few comparably young youngsters happily skipping around the studios, being sheparded by 3-2-1's kind, professional and talented teachers.
Well, my little one had the time of her young life and amazingly learned so much about memorizing lines and performing them in front of the camera -- even though she could hardly read at first!
The bug for acting and being in front of the camera has only increased in the time since.  Fast forward a few years (after having not pursued a professional career for our daughter back then -- although we should have!), and we brought her back to 3-2-1 Acting Studios because as a family we all decided that our pride and joy should pursue her passion professionally. That's not to mention that we now live in Agoura Hills -- 40 miles away from La Crescenta -- but after having a strange time checking out a much larger 'modeling and acting school,' we knew we had to return to Ms. Mae!
Cutting to the chase, after this past summer's Showcase class, she showcased and got an agent (the one from four years previous also wanted her again!)! Since then, she's booked a few great gigs, including an integral part in an arthouse feature film and background for Modern Family! Through the casting sites, I've gotten her around 20 auditions so far (in three months), and we're happily optimistic about her career prognosis!
Bottom line, Ms. Mae and her wonderful acting studio is where my daughter gained the confidence to be her most genuine, delightful, performing self! From all of us, THANK YOU MS. MAE!!!< /Text>

< Text>
We always take our cars to this place as it's conveniently close to our home. Line is never long, our cars are always serviced quickly. We've tried several of their options and they do an OK job regardless of what you pay for. I mean, the cars always leave cleaner than they were before but they never do an excellent job. I took my car just a few days ago and bought the basic wash for 7.99, basic exterior only. The car had bird poop right above the windshield, in a very visible spot; when I returned home I could still see the bird poop which, by the way, it's not that hard to get rid of. The back door and window were the least prepped I guess; there was no major difference between the before and after. I think they could prep better. I didn't want to go back though so I just let it go. I guess you get what you pay for, right?< /Text>

I took my 2 1/2 year old grandson and my friends 7 1/2 year old son there today(Friday 7/19/19) there were lots of older kids there, preteen to earlyteen that were rough housing, punching each other, calling each other names, cussing, climbing on top of the train and other structures, pushing the little kids out of the way. < Text>
I got a Chicken McGriddle and a Chicken Biscuit sandwich from the breakfast $1/$2/$3 menu. Total cost was 2 for $3.50. I really liked the McGriddle sandwich which used moist pancakes instead of bread or biscuit. I would definitely order this again. It tasted like there was some syrup on it but I couldn't find any. I'd ask for it next time. The biscuit was good but a bit dry with no sauce or butter. The chicken in both sandwiches was battered, fried and seasoned. Well priced, tasty, and fast from order to pickup, I'd order these items again.<//Text>

<review>Gotta say this is one busy Micky D's. I was  going to pass this place up upon my initial impressions because how crowded it was in the morning. For real, the parking lot is double most or triple some McDonads and it was almost to full capacity. Then the drive-thru lines had about 10 vehicles in line wrapping around to the street. Well, to my surprise the line inside was super quick! I was in and out in a snap :-)

What I liked...
* Nice new looking remodel.
* Super large parking lot with easy parking.
* Preparation of food was very fast given the amount of customers in the morning rush.
* It was an extra bonus that both the employees and store patrons were unusually friendly and smiling. That's not the reputation Long Beach has, but certainly nice to see :-)

What I didn't like...
* Nothing comes to mind.

Food = as expected

<Text>The only Mickie D's in San Pedro proper! A popular and happenin' spot to eat inside or drive thru! Okay, well maybe "happenin'" is being a little silly... Still, this joint is busy all day long, especially at the traditional lunch and dinner times. However, this particular iteration of the franchise really tends to be well-kept, maintained and the service is above average for fast-food chains of this calibre(most of all, McDonald's, because so many of the franchise's locations survive strictly on name). I have had very good experiences with the employees here for the most part. And the crusty-looking riff-raff crawling across the town somehow doesn't assert a distracting presence here as they often do at low-cost, high-volume establishments. Their bathroom is even public access, no lock! A strong example of this chain, made more pronounced by the lack of others nearby</Text><pictures>None</pictures><Name>Devon Harlon</Name></record>
